<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="68043" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="68043">Description</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="68043">
Male length 2.8 mm (including wing). Body yellowish. Vertex brownish-yellow, with pair of small dark brown apical spots (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F7002636" captionText="Figure 3. Anufrievia confluensa sp. nov. A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Habitus, lateral view; C. Head and thorax, dorsal view; D. Face." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e68043.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/544894" pageId="0" pageNumber="68043">3</figureCitation>
A and C). Eyes grey. Face pale milky yellow, anteclypeus and frontoclypeus light brownish (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F7002636" captionText="Figure 3. Anufrievia confluensa sp. nov. A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Habitus, lateral view; C. Head and thorax, dorsal view; D. Face." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e68043.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/544894" pageId="0" pageNumber="68043">3</figureCitation>
B and D). Pronotum and scutellum brownish-yellow and anterior margin of scutellum with black triangles (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F7002636" captionText="Figure 3. Anufrievia confluensa sp. nov. A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Habitus, lateral view; C. Head and thorax, dorsal view; D. Face." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e68043.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/544894" pageId="0" pageNumber="68043">3</figureCitation>
A and C). Forewing beige (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F7002636" captionText="Figure 3. Anufrievia confluensa sp. nov. A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Habitus, lateral view; C. Head and thorax, dorsal view; D. Face." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e68043.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/544894" pageId="0" pageNumber="68043">3</figureCitation>
A and B). Abdominal apodemes very short, not extended to 3rd sternite (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F7002648" captionText="Figure 4. Anufrievia confluensa sp. nov. A. Abdominal apodemes; B. Pygofer lobe; C. Pygofer dorsal appendage, lateral view; D. Subgenital plate; E. Style; F. Aedeagus, ventral view; G. Aedeagus, lateral view; H. Connective." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e68043.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/536063" pageId="0" pageNumber="68043">4</figureCitation>
A).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="68043" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="68043">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="68043">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="68043">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer lobe broad, with dense microsetae near dorso-caudal margin and several peg-like setae on outer surface (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F7002648" captionText="Figure 4. Anufrievia confluensa sp. nov. A. Abdominal apodemes; B. Pygofer lobe; C. Pygofer dorsal appendage, lateral view; D. Subgenital plate; E. Style; F. Aedeagus, ventral view; G. Aedeagus, lateral view; H. Connective." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e68043.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/536063" pageId="0" pageNumber="68043">4</figureCitation>
B). Pygofer dorsal appendage broadened at base, tapering towards apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F7002648" captionText="Figure 4. Anufrievia confluensa sp. nov. A. Abdominal apodemes; B. Pygofer lobe; C. Pygofer dorsal appendage, lateral view; D. Subgenital plate; E. Style; F. Aedeagus, ventral view; G. Aedeagus, lateral view; H. Connective." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e68043.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/536063" pageId="0" pageNumber="68043">4</figureCitation>
C). Subgenital plate slightly concave near middle area, with three macrosetae on lateral margin, row of short stout setae along upper margin from sub-base to apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F7002648" captionText="Figure 4. Anufrievia confluensa sp. nov. A. Abdominal apodemes; B. Pygofer lobe; C. Pygofer dorsal appendage, lateral view; D. Subgenital plate; E. Style; F. Aedeagus, ventral view; G. Aedeagus, lateral view; H. Connective." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e68043.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/536063" pageId="0" pageNumber="68043">4</figureCitation>
D). Style with two points at apex; pre-apical lobe small (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F7002648" captionText="Figure 4. Anufrievia confluensa sp. nov. A. Abdominal apodemes; B. Pygofer lobe; C. Pygofer dorsal appendage, lateral view; D. Subgenital plate; E. Style; F. Aedeagus, ventral view; G. Aedeagus, lateral view; H. Connective." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e68043.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/536063" pageId="0" pageNumber="68043">4</figureCitation>
E). Aedeagal shaft straight and flat in lateral view, but long and slim in ventral view; gonopore arising from ventral surface, reaching two thirds of aedeagal shaft; dorsal apodeme well developed (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F7002648" captionText="Figure 4. Anufrievia confluensa sp. nov. A. Abdominal apodemes; B. Pygofer lobe; C. Pygofer dorsal appendage, lateral view; D. Subgenital plate; E. Style; F. Aedeagus, ventral view; G. Aedeagus, lateral view; H. Connective." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e68043.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/536063" pageId="0" pageNumber="68043">4</figureCitation>
F and G). Connective Y-shaped, two arms slender, central lobe absent (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F7002648" captionText="Figure 4. Anufrievia confluensa sp. nov. A. Abdominal apodemes; B. Pygofer lobe; C. Pygofer dorsal appendage, lateral view; D. Subgenital plate; E. Style; F. Aedeagus, ventral view; G. Aedeagus, lateral view; H. Connective." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e68043.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/536063" pageId="0" pageNumber="68043">4</figureCitation>
H).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="68043" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="68043">Etymology</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="68043">
The new species is named from the Latin word &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="68043">confluensus</emphasis>
&quot;, referring to the connective stem fused with a long process (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F7002648" captionText="Figure 4. Anufrievia confluensa sp. nov. A. Abdominal apodemes; B. Pygofer lobe; C. Pygofer dorsal appendage, lateral view; D. Subgenital plate; E. Style; F. Aedeagus, ventral view; G. Aedeagus, lateral view; H. Connective." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e68043.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/536063" pageId="0" pageNumber="68043">4</figureCitation>
H).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="68043" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="68043">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="68043">
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. akazu" pageId="0" pageNumber="68043" rank="species" species="akazu">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="68043">A. akazu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Matsumura, S" journalOrPublisher="Insecta Matsumurana" pageId="0" pageNumber="68043" pagination="93 - 120" refId="B6966439" refString="Matsumura, S, 1932. A revision of the Palaearctic and Oriental typhlocybid-genera with descriptions of new species and new genera. Insecta Matsumurana 6 (3): 93 - 120" title="A revision of the Palaearctic and Oriental typhlocybid-genera with descriptions of new species and new genera" volume="6" year="1932">Matsumura 1932</bibRefCitation>
), but can be recognised by the subapical ventral surface without paired short processes and pygofer appendage not bifurcate at apex.
</paragraph>
